==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Palace
<hw>Pal"ace</hw> <pr>(p⟦acr⟧l"⟦asl⟧s; 48)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>palais</ets>, F. <ets>palais</ets>, fr. L. <ets>palatium</ets>, fr.
<ets>Palatium</ets>, one of the seven hills of Rome, on which Augustus
had his residence. Cf. <er>Paladin</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The residence of a sovereign, including the lodgings
of high officers of state, and rooms for business, as well as halls for
ceremony and reception.</def> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The official residence of a bishop or other
distinguished personage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Loosely, any unusually magnificent or stately
house.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Palace car</b></col>. <cd>See under <er>Car</er>.</cd> --
<col><b>Palace court</b></col>, <cd>a court having jurisdiction of
personal actions arising within twelve miles of the palace at Whitehall.
The court was abolished in 1849.</cd> <mark>[Eng.]</mark> <rj><au>Mozley
& W.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Palacious</ent>⟦br⟧
